{"questionId":"11864","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of the horizontal asymptote.&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\to&nbsp; \\pm \\infty {\\text{,}}\\,\\,f\\left( x \\right) \\to 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;so the equation of the horizontal asymptote is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y =0\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11864","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.4b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of the horizontal asymptote.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.13—Rational functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}